l-align: -0.338ex; width:68.05ex; height:2.676ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \h=
bar =3D1.054\ 571\ 817\ 646\times 10^{-34}\ \mathrm {J{\cdot }s} =3D6.582\ =
119\ 569\ 509\times 10^{-16}\ \mathrm {eV{\cdot }s} .}"></span>
</p><p>The above relations also allow expressing the <a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/Mean_lifetime" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Mean lifet=
ime">mean lifetime</a> <i>=CF=84</i> of an unstable particle (in seconds) i=
n terms of its <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Decay_width" class=
=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Decay width">decay width</a> =CE=93 (in eV) via <=
span class=3D"nowrap">=CE=93 =3D <i>=C4=A7</i>/<i>=CF=84</i></span>. For ex=
ample, the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/B_meson" title=3D"B mes=
on"><span class=3D"" style=3D"white-space:nowrap;">B<span class=3D"nowrap">=
<span style=3D"display:inline-block;margin-bottom:-0.3em;vertical-align:0.8=
em;line-height:1.0em;font-size:80%;text-align:left"><sup style=3D"font-size=
:inherit;line-height:inherit;vertical-align:baseline">0</sup><br><sub style=
=3D"font-size:inherit;line-height:inherit;vertical-align:baseline"></sub></=
span></span></span> meson</a> has a lifetime of 1.530(9)&nbsp;<a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Picosecond" title=3D"Picosecond">picoseconds</a=
>, mean decay length is <span class=3D"nowrap"><i>c=CF=84</i> =3D <span cla=
ss=3D"nowrap"><span data-sort-value=3D"6996459699999999999=E2=99=A0"></span=
>459.7&nbsp;=CE=BCm</span></span>, or a decay width of <span class=3D"nowra=
p"><span data-sort-value=3D"6977689256324707400=E2=99=A0"></span>4.302(25)<=
span style=3D"margin-left:0.25em;margin-right:0.15em;">=C3=97</span>10<sup>=
=E2=88=924</sup>&nbsp;eV</span>.
</p><p>Conversely, the tiny meson mass differences responsible for <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neutral_particle_oscillation" title=3D"Ne=
utral particle oscillation">meson oscillations</a> are often expressed in t=
he more convenient inverse picoseconds.
</p><p>Energy in electronvolts is sometimes expressed through the wavelengt=
h of light with photons of the same energy:
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
