<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Molar_energy">Molar energy<=
/h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[=
</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DElectronvolt=
&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D10" title=3D"Edit section: Molar energy"><=
span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span><=
/div>
<p>One <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mole_(unit)" title=3D"Mole =
(unit)">mole</a> of particles given 1&nbsp;eV of energy each has approximat=
ely 96.5&nbsp;kJ of energy =E2=80=93 this corresponds to the <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Faraday_constant" title=3D"Faraday constant">Far=
aday constant</a> (<i>F</i> =E2=89=88 <span class=3D"nowrap"><span data-sor=
t-value=3D"7004964850000000000=E2=99=A0"></span>96<span style=3D"margin-lef=
t:.25em;">485</span>&nbsp;C=E2=8B=85mol<sup>=E2=88=921</sup></span>), where=
 the energy in joules of <i>n</i> moles of particles each with energy <i>E<=
/i>&nbsp;eV is equal to <i>E</i>=C2=B7<i>F</i>=C2=B7<i>n</i>.
</p>
